To make your layout responsive and stack the sidebar and main content on smaller screens (like mobile devices), you can use media queries in combination with Flexbox or Grid. Here’s how you can achieve this:

### Using Flexbox

```css
.container {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap; /* Allow items to wrap to the next line on smaller screens */
}

.sidebar {
    flex: 0 0 30%; /* 30% width on larger screens */
    background-color: #f0f0f0;
    padding: 10px;
    box-sizing: border-box;
}

.main-content {
    flex: 0 0 70%; /* 70% width on larger screens */
    background-color: #ffffff;
    padding: 10px;
    box-sizing: border-box;
}

/* Media query for mobile devices */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    .sidebar, .main-content {
        flex: 0 0 100%; /* 100% width on smaller screens */
    }
}
```

### Using Grid

```css
.container {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 30% 70%; /* 30% for sidebar, 70% for main content on larger screens */
}

.sidebar {
    background-color: #f0f0f0;
